{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/9864", "repo": "rails", "body": "About the comments: Will keep in mind the next time\r\n\r\nWhile scanning through Error model, I found the tr(\".\",\"_\") and humanize on the result in `full_messages`.\r\n\r\nThe behaviour for having `_` in the name is different than having a `.`\r\n\r\nEx: \r\n`Model.nestedattr => Model nestedattr`\r\nbut `model_test` maps to `model_test` itself\r\n\r\nTest for previous behaviour is present the latter isn't, so added the test.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n", "_id": {"$oid": "5237e604bd3543c1510093ee"}, "issue_id": 9864, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/15286307", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/9864#issuecomment-15286307", "updated_at": "2013-03-22T08:45:28Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vipulnsward/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vipulnsward/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vipulnsward/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vipulnsward/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/vipulnsward", "login": "vipulnsward", "gravatar_id": "f459742822cf8347e83d5c445378a934", "html_url": "https://github.com/vipulnsward", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vipulnsward/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vipulnsward/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vipulnsward/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/f459742822cf8347e83d5c445378a934?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fdf97766e135d7b474bee10e0365d54bf.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vipulnsward/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 567626, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vipulnsward/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2013-03-22T08:45:28Z", "id": 15286307, "owner": "rails"}
